This robot works on infrared light detection. There is an IR remote, held by the robot operator, and IR receiver which is mounted on the robot.
Each button on the remote encodes a particular code (usually hexadecimal, of the format 0x15,0x46,etc.). 
You can customise any button to do any operation you like. In this project, I selected buttons 2,8,4 and 6 to correspond to forward, backward, leftward and rightward movement of the robot. I selected button 
5 to be the "STOP" button.
